t%20projects%20in%20Somalia%2C%20and%20planned%20to%20make%20an%20impact%20in%20the%20nonprofit%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20I%20returned%20to%20the%20US%2C%20the%20only%20job%20I%20could%20find%20was%20100%25%20commission%20sales.%20One%20of%20my%20cold%20calls%20was%20to%20a%20man%20named%20William%20Bouweiri%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstretch-limo-death-suv-black-car-uber-lyft-sprinter-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eowned%20a%20small%20limousine%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Northern%20Virginia.%20That%20call%20changed%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20dating%2C%20and%20four%20months%20later%2C%20he%20asked%20me%20to%20leave%20my%20job%20and%20join%20him%20in%20his%20business.%20I%20did%2C%20and%20within%20a%20year%2C%20we%20were%20married.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f539f932-a796-45e5-83f1-dc1cadad3c05%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EReston%20Limousine%20was%20a%20small%20operation%20when%20I%20came%20on%20board%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20focused%20on%20corporate%20clients%20%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehe%20had%20only%20five%20cars%20and%20made%20%24200%2C000%20in%20yearly%20revenue.%20But%20I%20saw%20potential%20elsewhere.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprom-dresses-style-through-the-decades-photos%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20pushed%20for%20proms%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20weddings%2C%20and%20eventually%20government%20contracts.%20I%20cold-called%20brides%20from%20purchased%20lists%2C%20and%20within%20a%20year%2C%20we%20were%20doing%20100%20weddings%20every%20weekend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20'90s%2C%20we%20were%20in%20the%20right%20place%20at%20the%20right%20time.%20We%20landed%20government%20shuttle%20contracts%2C%20and%20tech%20companies%20like%20AOL%20became%20clients.%20Revenue%20soared%20to%20%245%20million.%20Eventually%2C%20we%20grew%20to%20240%20vehicles%20with%20contracts%20across%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3C