n%2C%20a%20move%20Michael%20Vaughan%20considers%20bold.%20Gill%20will%20lead%20India%20in%20the%20upcoming%20five-match%20series%20against%20England%2C%20marking%20the%20start%20of%20the%20WTC%202025-27%20cycle.%20Vaughan%20believes%20this%20tour%20could%20usher%20in%20a%20new%20era%20for%20Indian%20Test%20cricket%2C%20with%20Rishabh%20Pant%20as%20vice-captain.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Axiom's%20CEO%20explains%20to%20us%20what%20a%20%2470%20million%20ticket%20to%20space%20gets%20you%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ax2%20SpaceX%20launch%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683eff4c6ffb6822ec61f2f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAxiom%20Space%20CEO%20Tejpaul%20Bhatia%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20ticket%20price%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bdrop%20in%20the%20bucket%26quot%3B%20compared%20to%20what%20it%20would%20cost%20a%20country%20to%20build%20a%20space%20program.%3Cp%3EAxiom%20Space%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAxiom%20Space%20offers%20space%20tickets%20with%20yearlong%20astronaut%20training%20priced%20around%20%2470%20million.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20price%20is%20higher%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblue-origin%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBlue%20Origin%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Virgin%20Galactic%2C%20and%20is%20geared%20toward%20advancing%20science.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAxiom's%20missions%2C%20including%20one%20set%20to%20launch%20Monday%2C%20visit%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20for%20about%20two%20weeks%20of%20extensive%20research%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETickets%20to%20space%20aren't%20cheap%20%E2%80%94%20but%20Axiom%20Space%20is%20a%20company%20pricing%20its%20offerings%20at%20the%20decidedly%20high%20end%20of%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20tickets%2C%20which%20cost%20roughly%20%2470%20million%2C%20are%20steep%20compared%20to%20other%20human%20spaceflight%20options%20offered%20by%20space%20tourism%20companies.%20For%20context%2C%20Blue%20Origin%20requires%20a%20%24150%2C000%20refundable%20deposit%20for%20a%20ticket%20to%20space%2C%20and%20auctioned%20off%20a%20ticket%20for%20%2428%20million.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvirgin-galactic-blue-origin-spacex-commercial-space-flights-tourism-cost-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EVirgin%20Galactic%20tickets%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20previously%20priced%20at%20%24600%2C000%2C%20and%20are%20expected%20to%20go%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20why%20is%20Axiom's%20offering%20priced%20so%20much%20higher%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20starters%2C%20the%20destination%20is%20different.%20Unlike%20other%20human%20spaceflight%20missions%2C%20like%20Blue%20Origin's%20New%20Shepard%20trip%2C%20Axiom%20Space%20missions%20extend%20beyond%20an%2011-minute%20experience%2C%20involving%20much%20more%20than%20a%20rocket%20trip%20into%20weightlessness%20and%20a%20quick%20return%20to%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20you'll%20visit%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECEO%20Tejpaul%20Bhatia%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Axiom%20Space's%20private%20astronaut%20missions%20to%20the%20ISS%20last%20around%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBhatia%20added%20that%20the%20%2470%20million%20price%20tag%20doesn't%20just%20cover%20a%20ticket%20to%20space%2C%20but%20a%20yearlong%20program%20to%20become%20a%20trained%20astronaut.%20The%20company%20told%20BI%20that%20Axiom%20Space's%20private%20astronauts%20undergo%20training%20that%20meets%20NASA%20standards%2C%20though%20it%20isn't%20quite%20as%20robust%20as%20what%20is%20required%20of%20NASA%20astronauts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20full-on%20enterprise%2C%26quot%3B%20Bhatia%2C%20who%20hasn't%20taken%20a%20trip%20himself%20but%20told%20BI%20he's%20often%20referred%20to%20by%20others%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bastronaut%20whisperer.%26quot%3B%20Private%20individuals%20who%20paid%20their%20way%20to%20space%20end%20up%20investing%20far%20more%20than%20just%20the%20ticket%20price%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20360-degree%20view%20from%20inside%20the%20ISS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683f0c25ca50259add4d8336%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20360-degree%20view%20from%20inside%20the%20ISS%20on%20AX-3.%3Cp%3EAxiom%20Space%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Axiom%20Space%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20trips%20are%20open%20to%20countries%2C%20space%20agencies%2C%20researchers%2C%20organizations%2C%20and%20individuals%3B%20however%2C%20they%20have%20to%20align%20with%20the%20company's%20mission%20and%20overall%20objectives.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20exact%20price%20is%20determined%20on%20a%20case-by-case%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20unlike%20other%20companies%20offering%20human%20spaceflight%2C%20Axiom%20Space%20doesn't%20manufacture%20its%20own%20rockets%20or%20spaceships.%20It%20forms%20contracts%20with%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-launch%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESpaceX%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20send%20trained%20astronauts%20to%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20said%20that%20the%20missions%20also%20open%20opportunities%20for%20countries%20to%20access%20space%20beyond%20the%20partners%20of%20the%20ISS.%20Its%20coming%20mission%2C%20AX-4%2C%20launching%20a%20crewed%20mission%20on%20Monday%2C%20includes%20government%20contracts%20with%20India%2C%20Poland%2C%20and%20Hungary.%20At%20the%20government%20level%2C%20Bhatia%20said%20the%20ticket%20price%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bdrop%20in%20the%20bucket%26quot%3B%20compared%20to%20what%20it%20would%20cost%20a%20country%20to%20build%20a%20space%20program%20to%20send%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20talking%20like%20orders%20of%20magnitude%20less%2C%26quot%3B%20Bhatia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20spent%20about%20%2425.8%20billion%20on%20Project%20Apollo%20between%201960%20and%201973.%20If%20you%20factor%20in%20inflation%2C%20that%20would%20come%20out%20to%20around%20%24237%20billion%20in%20today's%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faxiom-space-x-launch-first-ever-private-astronaut-mission-iss-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecompany's%20human%20spaceflight%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20just%20one%20part%20of%20its%20larger%20mission%20to%20build%20the%20world's%20first%20commercial%20space%20station%20to%20succeed%20the%20ISS%2C%20which%20has%20long%20served%20as%20a%20platform%20for%20international%20crews%20and%20scientific%20research%2C%20and%20is%20set%20to%20expire%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226479b894-6d43-41c3-9521-2fad246e3978%5C%22%3EDedicating%20a%20year%20to%20training%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBhatia%20said%20the%20roughly%20yearlong%20journey%20begins%20with%20the%20decision%20to%20go%20to%20space%2C%20a%20process%20that%20involves%20working%20with%20customers%20to%20develop%20the%20mission's%20criteria%20and%20firming%20up%20contractual%20considerations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20there%2C%20astronauts%20typically%20start%20training%20eight%20months%20to%20a%20year%20before%20launch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20to%20dedicate%2C%20effectively%2C%20that%20year%20of%20their%20life%20to%20training%2C%26quot%3B%20Bhatia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAxiom%20Space%20partners%20with%20NASA%2C%20Space%2C%20ESA%2C%20JAXA%2C%20and%20others%20to%20conduct%20the%20training%2C%20which%20includes%20700%20to%201%2C000%20hours%20of%20instruction%20in%20safety%2C%20health%2C%20ISS%20systems%2C%20and%20launch%20operations%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20mission%20is%20set%20in%20stone%2C%20the%20individuals%20begin%20initial%20onboarding%20and%20mission-specific%20training.%20That%20includes%20familiarization%20with%20mission%20objectives%2C%20safety%20protocols%2C%20and%20team-building.%20Then%20the%20astronauts%20undergo%20detailed%20training%20at%20SpaceX%20facilities%2C%20where%20they%20learn%20about%20the%20company's%20Dragon%20spacecraft%20and%20Falcon%209%20launch%20vehicle.%20The%20training%20focuses%20on%20system%20operations%2C%20emergency%20procedures%2C%20and%20full-mission%20simulations%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crew%20also%20goes%20through%20extensive%20training%20at%20NASA's%20Johnson%20Space%20Center%20on%20ISS%20operations%2C%20including%20payload%20management%2C%20microgravity%20adaptation%2C%20and%20emergency%20preparedness%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20launch%2C%20Axiom%20Space%20astronauts%20have%20to%20receive%20approval%20from%20international%20partners%20to%20go%20forth%20on%20the%20mission.%20About%20two%20weeks%20before%20takeoff%2C%20the%20crew%20enters%20quarantine%2C%20a%20protocol%20that%20predates%20COVID.%20Bhatia%20added%20that%20starting%20a%20month%20before%20launch%2C%20the%20crew%20has%20to%20wear%20masks%20during%20any%20in-person%20interactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bcaf84bf-9e50-4298-8d5e-2644cef2c0bf%5C%22%3E'Every%20minute'%20of%20the%20flight%20is%20accounted%20for%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20spending%20as%20much%20as%20%2470%20million%20for%20a%20ticket%20to%20space%2C%20the%20experience%20is%20far%20from%20luxurious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20rugged%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20Bhatia%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it's%20%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20comfortable%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBhatia%20said%20the%20crew%20typically%20spends%20about%2014%20days%20at%20the%20ISS%2C%20although%20sometimes%20it's%20less%20or%20more%20depending%20on%20the%20dynamics%20of%20spaceflight%2C%20including%20weather%20considerations.%20Those%20two%20weeks%20consist%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20regimented%20routine%2C%26quot%3B%20involving%20hard%20science%20and%20research%2C%20Bhatia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20minute%20is%20accounted%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CEO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225568%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22AX-3%20mission%20specialist%20conducting%20research%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683f0d846ffb6822ec61f4ea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223712%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBhatia%20said%20the%20crew%20keeps%20a%20busy%20agenda%20during%20the%20span%20of%20the%20trip.%3Cp%3EAxiom%20Space%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mission%20also%20involves%20significant%20engagement%20with%20the%20public%20and%20media.%20Bhatia%20said%20crew%20members%20appear%20on%20prime-time%20news%20broadcasts%20live%20from%20the%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Bhatia%20said%20there%20can%20sometimes%20be%20technical%20difficulties%20or%20a%20transmission%20drop%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20everything%20is%20planned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20controlled%20systems%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Bhatia%20said%20and%20astronauts%20are%20prepared%20with%20the%20skills%20and%20knowledge%20needed%20for%20a%20successful%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20end%20of%20the%20trip%20ends%20with%20the%20Dragon%20Spacecraft%20making%20a%20%26quot%3Bsmall%20splashdown%26quot%3B%20in%20water%20and%20a%20period%20where%20the%20crew%20adjusts%20back%20to%20gravity.%20Once%20they%20land%2C%20crew%20members%20are%20given%20extensive%20medical%20evaluations%20before%20post-mission%20activities%20begin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e9b3bf5f-d76d-4e83-abb0-0c370336c5a5%5C%22%3EGrowing%20interest%20in%20private%20space%20exploration%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBhatia%20told%20BI%20that%20when%20he%20joined%20the%20space%20company%20as%20chief%20revenue%20officer%20four%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20shifted%20it%20toward%20government%20sales.%20Demand%20for%20the%20%2470%20million%20private%20ticket%20seems%20to%20be%20higher%2C%20he%20added.%20Bhatia%20said%20that%20the%20company%20has%20sold%20more%20private%20astronaut%20seats%20in%20that%20time%2C%20although%20they%20haven't%20flown%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20less%20about%20our%20ability%20to%20sell%20these%20tickets%2C%26quot%3B%20Bhatia%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20about%20an%20evolution%20in%20the%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20evolution%20is%20reflected%20in%20similar%20efforts%20by%20other%20companies%2C%20like%20Jeff%20Bezos'%20Blue%20Origin%2C%20which%20recently%20made%20headlines%20for%20its%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkaty-perry-blue-origin-space-mission-criticism-career-marketing-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efirst%20all-female%20crew%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20included%20Katy%20Perry%20and%20Bezos'%20fianc%C3%A9e%2C%20Lauren%20S%C3%A1nchez.%20When%20asked%20whether%20backlash%20toward%20that%20mission%20and%20commercial%20space%20travel%20in%20general%20might%20impact%20public%20support%20for%20high-cost%20missions%20like%20Axiom's%2C%20Bhatia%20said%20he%20wasn't%20concerned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20not%20being%20influenced%20by%20those%20headlines%2C%26quot%3B%20Bhatia%20said%20about%20the%20governments%20sending%20their%20citizens%20to%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBhatia%20said%20suborbital%20missions%20are%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20cool%26quot%3B%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bspace%20nut%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20multiple%20factors%20likely%20contributed%20to%20the%20backlash%2C%20all%20of%20which%20he%20felt%20could%20have%20been%20spun%20in%20a%20positive%20way.%20He%20said%20criticism%20may%20have%20been%20driven%20by%20a%20response%20to%20the%20company%20behind%20the%20mission%20or%20the%20crew%20who%20attended%20the%20trip.%20The%20CEO%20also%20said%20that%20there%20tends%20to%20be%20an%20overarching%20mindset%20that%20people%20shouldn't%20spend%20money%20on%20space%20when%20there%20are%20problems%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSpace%20and%20Earth%20are%20not%20mutually%20exclusive%2C%20they%20never%20have%20been%20and%20never%20will%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20Bhatia%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20humans%20are%20part%20of%20the%20universe%20and%20space%20is%20%26quot%3Bour%20environment%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20whether%20he%20plans%20to%20go%20to%20space%20soon%2C%20the%20CEO%20said%20he%20thinks%20eventually%20it%20will%20happen.%20For%20now%2C%20though%2C%20he%20said%20the%20focus%20is%20on%20getting%20others%20to%20fly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20become%20more%20of%20a%20mission%20for%20me%20to%20figure%20it%20out%20for%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20Bhatia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faxiom-space-ceo-70-million-dollar-ticket-iss-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749461521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683eff4c6ffb6822ec61f2f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faxiom-space-ceo-70-million-dollar-ticket-iss-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Axiom's%20crewed%20missions%20visit%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20for%20about%20two%20weeks%20of%20extensive%20research%20work%2C%20where%20%26quot%3Bevery%20minute%20is%20accounted%20for.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faxiom-space-ceo-70-million-dollar-ticket-iss-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Student%20Visa%20in%20the%20US%3A%20How%20to%20apply%20F-1%20Visa%20online%2C%20requirements%2C%20documents%20required%2C%20fees%20and%20other%20key%20information%22%2C%