0colourful%20and%20powerful%20symbol%20of%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community.%20First%20created%20in%20the%20late%201970s%20by%20artist%20and%20activist%20Gilbert%20Baker%2C%20it%20celebrates%20the%20beauty%20and%20diversity%20of%20people%20who%20identify%20as%20lesbian%2C%20gay%2C%20bisexual%2C%20transgender%2C%20and%20queer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20the%20rainbow%20flag%20has%20become%20one%20of%20the%20most%20recognised%20symbols%20of%20love%2C%20acceptance%2C%20and%20equality.%20You%E2%80%99ll%20often%20see%20it%20at%20pride%20parades%2C%20marches%2C%20and%20events%20that%20support%20LGBTQ%2B%20rights.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20rainbow%20flags%20can%20also%20be%20used%20in%20other%20contexts%20(like%20peace%20movements)%2C%20within%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20a%20vibrant%20reminder%20that%20everyone%20deserves%20to%20be%20proud%20of%20who%20they%20are%20and%20to%20be%20treated%20with%20dignity%20and%20respect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECloseted%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomeone%20who%20is%20closeted%20isn%E2%80%99t%20openly%20sharing%20their%20sexual%20orientation%20or%20gender%20identity%20with%20others.%20Coming%20out%20is%20a%20personal%20choice%3B%20everyone%20has%20their%20own%20timing%20and%20comfort%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20person%20might%20be%20out%20to%20some%20close%20friends%2C%20but%20not%20to%20family%20or%20coworkers.%20Fear%20of%20rejection%2C%20being%20treated%20differently%2C%20losing%20their%20job%2C%20or%20even%20facing%20harassment%20or%20violence%20are%20some%20of%20the%20reasons%20why%20one%20is%20still%20%E2%80%98not%20out%2C%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20and%20that%20is%20how%20we%20should%20be%20saying%20it%2C%20%E2%80%98not%20out.%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EComing%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImagine%20carrying%20a%20beautiful%20book%20with%20you%20that%20only%20you%20have%20read.%20The%20pages%20h